messageBody:
Okay, these probably aren't the most uplifting two poems to upload but
they are some of my favourite poetry.
Myxomatosis and True Love by Spike Milligan.

Like Daniel said: please criticise my (awful) spelling, after all you
learn faster from mistakes than just about anything else. :)

danielfilan wrote:
>
> Which reminds me, if it has any mistakes, please alert me so I can fix
> them.
>
> --- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com
> <mailto:Read_Alphabet%40yahoogroups.com>, "danielfilan" <danielfilan@...>
> wrote:
> >
> > Why don't we all upload our favourite poems in Quikscript? We could
> > have some sort of poetry collection, which would be a real help for
> > learners. Personally, I've already uploaded Jabberwocky, The
> > Three-toed Grynch by Odgen Nash and The Garden of Proserpine by
> > Algernon Swinbourne.
> >
>
>
